com.vmware.vcenter.ovf

Class LibraryItemTypes.ResourcePoolDeploymentSpec

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vmware.vcenter.ovf.LibraryItemTypes.ResourcePoolDeploymentSpec
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.bindings.StaticStructure, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Structure, java.io.Serializable
    Enclosing interface:
    LibraryItemTypes

    public static final class LibraryItemTypes.ResourcePoolDeploymentSpec
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.StaticStructure
    The ResourcePoolDeploymentSpec class defines the deployment parameters that can be specified for the deploy() method where the deployment target is a resource pool. See LibraryItem.deploy(java.lang.String, java.lang.String, com.vmware.vcenter.ovf.LibraryItemTypes.DeploymentTarget, com.vmware.vcenter.ovf.LibraryItemTypes.ResourcePoolDeploymentSpec).

        public java.util.List<com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Structure> getAdditionalParameters()
        Additional OVF parameters that may be needed for the deployment. Additional OVF parameters may be required by the OVF descriptor of the OVF package in the library item. Examples of OVF parameters that can be specified through this property include, but are not limited to:

      • getVmConfigSpec

        public LibraryItemTypes.VmConfigSpec getVmConfigSpec()
        The getVmConfigSpec() is used for virtual machine configuration settings including hardware specifications to use in place of the OVF descriptor. If set, the OVF descriptor acts as a disk descriptor. Fields in the ResourcePoolDeploymentSpec parameters such as getName() that overlap with settings in the getVmConfigSpec() are not overridden and will continue to be used. Similarly, storage settings in the ResourcePoolDeploymentSpec that affect the disks on the virtual machine namely getStorageMappings(), getStorageProfileId(), getStorageProvisioning() and getDefaultDatastoreId() will also be honored. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.2.0. If null, the relevant virtual machine specifications in the OVF descriptor of the OVF template will be used.
        Returns:
        The current value of the property.

      • setVmConfigSpec

        public void setVmConfigSpec(LibraryItemTypes.VmConfigSpec vmConfigSpec)
        The getVmConfigSpec() is used for virtual machine configuration settings including hardware specifications to use in place of the OVF descriptor. If set, the OVF descriptor acts as a disk descriptor. Fields in the ResourcePoolDeploymentSpec parameters such as getName() that overlap with settings in the getVmConfigSpec() are not overridden and will continue to be used. Similarly, storage settings in the ResourcePoolDeploymentSpec that affect the disks on the virtual machine namely getStorageMappings(), getStorageProfileId(), getStorageProvisioning() and getDefaultDatastoreId() will also be honored. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.2.0. If null, the relevant virtual machine specifications in the OVF descriptor of the OVF template will be used.
        Parameters:
        vmConfigSpec - New value for the property.
